---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { runBuildValidation } from '../lib/build-validate';

await runBuildValidation();
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout title="Vaccine Safety Signals">
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Unmasked: Vaccine Safety Signals</h1>
    <p class="lede">A structured presentation of the U.S. Senate Permanent Subcommittee on Investigations' April 2026 interim report and the underlying records published with it. The site centers the evidence: contemporaneous emails, the masking phenomenon in VAERS data mining, and the MGPS / RGPS comparison that drives the story.</p>
  </section>
  <aside class="key-points" aria-labelledby="key-points-heading">
    <h2 id="key-points-heading">Key Points</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The FDA's vaccine safety monitoring system has a known flaw called &ldquo;masking&rdquo; — when similar products dominate the database, real warning signs can get hidden because the products end up being compared against themselves.</li>
      <li>This happened with the COVID-19 mRNA vaccines (Pfizer and Moderna), where masking was roughly eight times more likely than with other vaccines.</li>
      <li>A senior FDA scientist, Dr. Ana Szarfman, applied a better method (RGPS) and found over 20 hidden safety signals — including sudden cardiac death, Bell's palsy, heart attacks, blood clots, and dementia.</li>
      <li>When she reported these findings to FDA leadership in 2021, she was told to stop, partly out of concern her work could fuel anti-vaccine sentiment.</li>
      <li>The FDA never adopted the improved method, and the routine weekly COVID-19 vaccine data-mining reports were discontinued in July 2022 — around the same time outside groups were filing public records requests for them.</li>
    </ul>
  </aside>
  <section class="modes">
    <a class="mode" href={`${base}explainer/`}>
      <h2>Explainer</h2>
      <p>What is signal masking?<br />A plain-language walkthrough.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="mode" href={`${base}timeline/`}>
      <h2>Timeline</h2>
      <p>Dated chronology, November 2020 to today, with citations and source documents.</p>
    </a>
    <a class="mode" href={`${base}documents/`}>
      <h2>Document archive</h2>
      <p>Searchable record of every Subcommittee-published exhibit.</p>
    </a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Hero matches main's width (50rem); the modes grid below uses the
     same width, so the boxes line up flush with the hero text. */
  .hero { margin: 2rem auto; }
  .hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 4.4vw, 2.5rem);
    margin: 0 0 0.5em;
    line-height: 1.15;
    text-wrap: balance;
    white-space: nowrap;
    text-align: center;
  }
  /* text-wrap: pretty balances the last few lines of the paragraph so we
     don't get an orphan word on its own line. */
  .lede { font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--color-muted); text-wrap: pretty; }
  /* Key Points callout: bordered box with a teal accent stripe down the
     left, signalling "summary" without competing with the three mode
     boxes below for the visitor's attention. */
  .key-points {
    margin: 2.5rem 0 0;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem 1.25rem 1.4rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: 6px;
    background: white;
  }
  .key-points h2 {
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }
  .key-points ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
  }
  .key-points li {
    font-size: 0.97rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .key-points li:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .modes { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1.5rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .modes { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  .mode {
    display: block;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    /* Solid black border at rest; on hover an outline of the same color
       appears flush against the outer edge of the border — visually
       thickening the edge from 1px to 2px without any grid-layout
       shift (outline doesn't take up box-model space). */
    border: 1px solid #000;
    border-radius: 6px;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--color-text);
    background: white;
    box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.03);
  }
  .mode:hover {
    outline: 1px solid #000;
    outline-offset: 0;
  }
  .mode h2 { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-accent); }
  .mode p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; }
</style>
